                        "Master takes writes (insert/delete/update); slaves serve reads; usually more slaves than masters (p. 12).",
                        "Replication gives better performance, reliability, and high availability (pp. 12-13).",
                        "Slave failure -> reads go to master/healthy slaves; master failure -> promote a slave, run recovery scripts (p. 13).",
                        "App reads from a slave and sends all data-modifying ops to the master (p. 14).",
