                        "A **key-value store** is a non-relational database where each unique **key** maps to an associated **value** (a \"key-value pair\") (p. 87). The key must be unique and is the only handle for accessing the value. Keys can be plain text (`\"last_logged_in_at\"`) or hashed (`253DDEC4`); for performance, **a short key works better** (p. 87). The value can be a string, list, object, etc., and is treated as an **opaque object** by stores like Amazon Dynamo, Memcached, and Redis (p. 87). The store must support just two operations:\n"
