                        "Partitioning must spread data evenly and minimize movement on membership changes; consistent hashing solves both (p. 93).",
                        "Virtual nodes give automatic scaling and heterogeneity (count proportional to server capacity) (pp. 93-94).",
                        "Replicate over a configurable N servers by walking clockwise from the key and taking the first N — but only unique physical servers (p. 94).",
                        "Place replicas in distinct data centers connected by high-speed networks for reliability (p. 94).",
